				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>As the CRNM has pointed out, the collapse of the Doha negotiations will simply delay the implementation of the emergent deal on bananas which will serve to profoundly erode the margins of preference enjoyed by ACP banana suppliers. The deployment of aid-for-trade support to banana-sector restructuring in line with past EU programmes could well prove sufficient to secure ACP acceptance of the emergent deal.</p>
		</div>
		
